From the developers of famous astronomical app Star Walk, winner of the Apple Design Award 2010, loved by more than 10 million users worldwide.

Ever wanted to observe the International Space Station crossing your sky or find out where human-made satellites are right now? With Satellite Tracker, you can easily find out where satellites can be seen from different locations in the world and get predictions for their passes. 

MAIN FEATURES:

->  Tracking satellites in real-time
->  The most outstanding satellites with core info
->  Satellite flyby timer
->  Pass predictions
->  Hand-picked passes
->  The ability to set any location
->  Fly-with-satellite view
->  Satellite orbit over Earth

HOW TO USE THE APP:

Open Satellite Tracker, tap on the satellite icon in the upper right corner of the screen. You’ll see the Tracking List that contains two tabs: Tracked and All. In the Tracked tab, you can see satellites you’re following right now. It means that the app will always show you these satellites on the 3D Earth orbit and notify you about the closest passes. Add and remove items from this list easily by tapping on the “Track” or “Untrack” button.  

In the All tab, the Main Satellites category goes first. All other satellites are divided according to their missions for easy search:

- Communications
- Weather & Earth Resources
- Scientific
- Navigation
- Miscellaneous
- Space Debris

There is also the Special-Interest category that includes the Last 30 days’ launches, the Space Stations, the Brightest satellites.

*** The ISS is available by default. Other satellites are available when subscribed. The app contains ads which will be removed when subscribed. 

Subscription Information:

With a SATELLITES LIVE optional subscription, you get an instant ad-free access to tracking satellites live orbiting over Earth and in the sky, the timer for the next appearance, and alerts about the nearest flybys.

SATELLITES LIVE is a renewable subscription with 1-week FREE trial that gives you access to content from within the app on an ongoing basis. Payment will be charged to your iTunes account. At the end of each subscription duration (1 month), the subscription will automatically renew until you choose to cancel it and your account will be charged for renewal 24 hours prior to the end of the current period. Users can manage their subscriptions in their account settings on the App Store.

Privacy policy: http://vitotechnology.com/privacy-policy.html
Terms of use: http://vitotechnology.com/terms-of-use.html

Never miss satellites passing by in the sky with Satellite Tracker!
